{'text': "Legalization of drugs could be a good thing, if it were done properly. However, let's discuss legalizing drugs for recreational purposes."}
{'text': "What is more important, educating kids about drugs or legalizing them? The fact that you don't want to legalize drugs means you don't care about educating kids about drugs, right?"}
{'text': "I think we should legalize drugs for recreational purposes, but I wouldn't go so far as to legalize them for all purposes."}
{'text': 'The way I see it, there are three kinds of drugs that are legal in the United States today: marijuana, heroin, and prescription painkillers.'}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you'll also have to legalize the people who are already addicted to drugs, because they'll have no other choice but to become addicted to drugs too."}

{'text': 'If we legalized drugs, we would then be forced to deal with the other side of the coin: the price of drugs would skyrocket, which would in turn lead to an increase in demand, which would...'}
{'text': 'Legalization of drugs would prevent the government from coming into the business of regulating drugs.'}
{'text': "There's a difference between a person who does drugs recreationally, and someone who does drugs to get high."}
{'text': 'In an age of globalization, can we really trust the governments of other countries to keep their borders secure and free of drug smugglers?'}
{'text': 'Of course, our way of life depends on a constant supply of drugs, which is why we have to keep them cheap.'}
{'text': "We should only legalize drugs when there is full regulation and regulation alone doesn't work.\xa0 What's the point in having an open market if it doesn't bring in money to the country?"}
{'text': "If the government can allow people to consume alcohol, then it should be able to allow people to consume drugs. It doesn't make sense to say that one is okay and the other is not."}
{'text': "I'd rather see Congress focus on dealing with the real problem of drug abuse, and then we can talk about legalizing drugs once we've dealt with drug abuse."}

{'text': "Do you really want to legalize drugs? The effects of legalization will be more harmful than the effects of prohibition.\xa0 That's why I believe that legalizing drugs is not the way to go about this."}
{'text': 'There is a difference between drug use and drug addiction. Drug users are those who use drugs. They have the right to use drugs however they want.'}

{'text': "For everyone who has been listening to this whole article, you probably agree with me, right? Of course, I'm talking about you. The majority of people in this country probably agree with me."}
{'text': 'In any case, we should legalize prostitution and gambling as well, because there is no reason to prohibit them while legalizing drugs. After all, prostitution is also a form of sex work.'}
{'text': "The problem with legalizing drugs is that we'll have to deal with all the legal problems that we've dealt with for the last 60 years."}
{'text': "This discussion has mostly focused on drugs that are legal in the United States.\xa0 We shouldn't legalize any other drugs until we figure out a good way to deal with drug addiction."}
{'text': "The government doesn't have the right to try to change how you use drugs. You are the one who is responsible for yourself."}
{'text': "It's much easier to deal with the opiate epidemic (which is a result of the prohibition) if we legalize drugs, rather than keep them illegal."}
{'text': "If we started treating drug addiction as a health issue, rather than a criminal one, we'd have a much better chance of winning the war on drugs."}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs would do more harm than good.'}
{'text': "Legalization of drugs isn't going to change the fact that they are addictive and harmful to the body. In fact, the opposite is true."}
{'text': 'The fact is that marijuana is illegal, but the government has been around for a very long time.'}
{'text': "If we're going to talk about legalization of drugs, then let's talk about it in a way that doesn't make us go back to the 1930s, the 1960s, or even the 1950..."}
{'text': "That being said, I don't think it's necessary to legalize all drugs."}
{'text': 'When you legalize drugs, there will always be drug dealers who will sell drugs illegally.'}
{'text': 'The under-18 population is going to get addicted to drugs as soon as they have access to them.'}

{'text': 'A big reason why millions of Americans continue to use drugs is because the U.S. government and the media have created a generation of drug-abuse victims through a series of irresponsible policies.'}
{'text': "When drugs become legal, it's hard to tell how many people will start using drugs because they won't be forced to."}
{'text': "You know what? I don't care about the right to decide for yourself whether or not to use drugs."}

{'text': "Since we won't know how many people are going to be addicted to drugs until we legalize them, we might as well legalize drugs so we'll know how many people are going to be addicted to drugs..."}
{'text': "We can't stop everyone from consuming drugs, and we can't control what people eat and drink."}
{'text': "It doesn't really matter whether you use drugs recreationally or not."}
{'text': 'If a business owner wants to turn his store into a speakeasy, or a brothel, or whatever you want to call it, then he has the right to turn it into what he wants...'}
{'text': 'If we want to legalize drugs, we need to first legalize all drugs. And we need to legalize drugs before we can legalize anything else.'}
